According to the [[wikipedia:documentary hypothesis|documentary hypothesis]], the [[wikipedia:Torah|Torah]] is composed from a number of originally independent sources joined by a [[wikipedia:redaction|redactor]]. One of these supposed sources is named the [[wikipedia:Deuteronomist|"Deuteronomist source"]], due to its comprising the majority of the book of Deuteronomy. This prose source contains within it a law code and a poem thought to have been earlier separate sources - The Song of Moses.

There follows the reconstructed text of the Deuteronomist Source, using the [[wikipedia:King James Version|King James Translation]] of the Torah. 
